      "writtenOn": "2026-04-08T18:28:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "These functions were defined in the Zone class (see https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-fan-presence/+/85111). A \"zone\" here is basically a grouping of fans that defines fault handling for fans in said zone. Chassis are subdivided into one or more zones, and Chassis objects are managed here in the MultiChassisSystem class.\n\nFor single-chassis, there was just one fault handling config per system, so those fan status monitoring and power down rule functions were defined in the System class. Since there can now be multiple fault handling configs that apply to different fans in different chassis, I moved those functionalities to the zone to handle that.",
      "parentUuid": "a44b81ad_45db5895",
      "revId": "6831d57687b99d886a2f7e6621289ba640b2da87",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
